title: High Five construction December 2004

pageHeader.title: Construction of the High Five Interchange
pageHeader.subTitle: December 2004

text: The High Five Interchange was completed in November 2005.

images.caption: Looking north along the future northbound US 75 main lanes from one of the connection ramps. Dallas police interrogated me while I was on the ramp taking the photo. Fortunately, the officer received a more urgent call while interrogating me so he left the scene immediately.
Looking north along the future northbound US 75 main lanes. This will be the bottom level of the interchange.
Moving northward towards the main ramp zone.
Getting closer to the center of the interchange
In the center of the interchange.
In the center of the interchange.
This view shows the piers for the two remaining bridges for IH-635. Traffic was on the completed southernmost span. The three bridges will allow a 5-2-2-5 configuration for IH-635.

Looking east along IH-635. The concrete on the left is for the future westbound main lanes. The concrete in the middle is for the future HOT lanes. Traffic was using the future eastbound structure at the time of this photo. The ramp on the left is 1.4 miles long.
A wider-angle view at the same location.
Looking west at the piers for the future westbound IH-635 main lanes.
